comments: Capela (ATL) is absorbing the initial contact that occurs with Ivey (DET) and incidental contact occurs as Ivey attempts to move over the pick
Cunningham (DET) brushes Capela's (ATL) right arm and marginal contact occurs during his finish at the basket.
Hunter's (ATL) arm is slightly extended as he absorbs the marginal contact that occurs with Ivey (DET) at the end of the drive.

Ivey (DET) elevates into his shooting motion with his arm slightly extended and contact occurs with Hunter's (ATL) head. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Johnson (ATL) contests the jump shot attempt and avoids making contact with Knox II's (DET) arms.
Burks (DET) reaches for the ball and initiates contact with Murray's (ATL) left arm that affects his SQBR.
Ivey (DET) releases the in-bounds pass within 5 seconds.
Murray (ATL) briefly has a hand on Burks' (DET) hip, but he does not apply any force as Burks gathers into his shooting motion.  The contact should be deemed marginal.
Knox II (DET) commits a take foul on Bey (ATL).
Capela (ATL) cleanly blocks the shot attempt prior to when the ball reaches its apex.
